race.comment: BETTA THAN PRESLEY (1) continues to race honestly and rarely runs a poor race. He was narrowly beaten into third over this track and trip last time and looks well placed again with the claim. On the quick back-up, this shapes as his best chance yet to break through. JE REVE (2) was safely held in his stable debut after a lengthy 549-day absence but should strip fitter. His prior NSW form is strong enough to warrant respect in this company. SPLICED (4) is an Exceed And Excel mare on debut for the Tyrell yard and has trialled twice, winning the latest at home. She looks ready to make an immediate impact. GOLDARNIE (6) resumes and showed ability last prep, including a placing first-up at this track and trip. If she has improved, she's a genuine winning hope. KOTOR BAY (7) is another debutant with blinkers on and a sharp trial win under her belt. Keep very safe.
